.TH "ring_buffer_swap_cpu" 9 "ring_buffer_swap_cpu" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ring_buffer_swap_cpu \- swap a CPU buffer between two ring buffers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ring_buffer_swap_cpu
.BI "(struct trace_buffer *buffer_a "  ","
.BI "struct trace_buffer *buffer_b "  ","
.BI "int cpu "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buffer_a" 12
One buffer to swap with
.IP "buffer_b" 12
The other buffer to swap with
.IP "cpu" 12
the CPU of the buffers to swap
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is useful for tracers that want to take a "snapshot"
of a CPU buffer and has another back up buffer lying around.
it is expected that the tracer handles the cpu buffer not being
used at the moment.
